1.   addding a non root user -->> adduser username
                        then what is prompted and asked fill it .
                        After logout enter username in place of root and password of that user in place of toor.
     
     
     
     
 
2. setup openssh server-
              
                        sudo apt-get install openssh-server                 
                        #Port 22   //// if u want to change port number for ssh then replace # and change number as =>> Port 214
                        # Authentication:

                                  #LoginGraceTime 2m
                                  #PermitRootLogin prohibit-password convert to PermitRootLogin yes 
                                  #StrictModes yes
                                  #MaxAuthTries 6
                                  #MaxSessions 10
                                  
                                  
                                  
                                  
                                  
                                  
   Now open application puty in windows and enter ip address of working interface.
